description:
1. The Supergirl-Batgirl Plot! (written by Cary Bates)

    Why are Batgirl and Supergirl trying to sabotage the careers of their male counterparts?

  2. The Amazing Cube (Editors' Round Table choice / written by George Kashdan : reprinted from: Tales of the Unexpected #9)
    A gambler steals a "lucky" dice off a dying man... to his own misfortune!
name: The Supergirl-Batgirl Plot!

description:
The Three Ages of Superboy! comes in 3 parts:

  1. Land of the Pharaohs!

  2. The Secret of the Black Knight!

  3. The Wild West of Jesse James!

Superboy goes back in time, and finds three Red Kryptonite meteorites. How did they get there? What powers do they give him in each different time era?
name: The Three Ages of Superboy!

  2. "Jimmy Olsen Meets Cleopatra!" (Jimmy Olsen, Superman, Professor Potter) Did Professor Potter send Jimmy back in time or did something else happen?
  3. Moolah the Mystic (gag strip by Henry Boltinoff)
  4. "The Nine Lives of Jimmy Olsen!" (Jimmy Olsen, Superman, Lois Lane, Perry White, Lucy Lane / written by Edmond Hamilton, penciled and inked by John Forte. Reprinted in The Superman Family #180.

Jimmy gets a magic cat paw from a cat tribe giving him nine lives! But because he now takes all these risks, will he use them all up?

description:
First appearance of Shauna McCullough (Zippy Couriers).

There's a special feature this prog giving the story behind Steve Dillon's lost artwork for Judge Dredd epic 'City of the Damned' (prog 404), which went missing and had to be hastily redrawn at the eleventh hour. With the original artwork now found, this feature reprints the original 'lost' artwork and compares it to what was printed at the time.

description: Star Wars: Attack of the Clones is a seminal tale of the Star Wars mythos, unlocking some of the history and events that laid the foundation for the Rebel Alliance's epic struggle against the Empire as chronicled in the original Star Wars film trilogy. Featuring familiar characters as never seen before and introducing new players destined to become Star Wars icons, Episode II is a must-see film, and this graphic novel is a must-read for all Star Wars enthusiasts. Adapted by Henry Gilroy from the original screenplay by George Lucas and Jonathan Hales, and illustrated by Jan Duursema and Ray Kryssing. Make sure you catch this legendary series that's sure to please Star Wars fans of all ages.

The battle for the world continues to rage in issue 2 of Sword of Darkness, Marvel’s adaptation of Kinley MacGregor’s (a.k.a. Sherrilyn Kenyon) best–selling novel.
